nd cuts the company offered affected employees the option to relocate to its centralized offices apply for a new job at their location or leave the company with a severance package for former employees unable to relocate in  shaw attempted to begin developing an iptvbased platform for its television services however after experiencing issues developing the platform shaw took a  million writedown in june  and announced that it was licensing comcasts cloudbased x architecture in january  shaw launched its mobile television app freerange tv based on x infrastructure which allows shaw subscribers to stream selected tv channels and ondemand content freedom mobile divestment of media assetsedit on december   shaw announced its proposed acquisition of independent wireless provider wind mobile from its investors in a deal worth approximately  billion the transaction closed on march   under shaw the company was renamed freedom mobile in november  coinciding with the launch of its g lte network the acquisition of wind was funded by a reorganization in april  which saw the shaw media unit transferred to corus entertainment in exchange for  billion in cash and  class b nonvoting shares of corus the sale did not include shaws  stake in the shomi streaming service and cjbntv kenora shomi was shut down in november  and cjbntv kenora was shut down in january  on january   shaw announced the launch of bluesky—a new iptvbased television service based on comcasts x platform the service was initially made available in calgary other activitiesedit shaw is the parent of shaw broadcast services previously shaw satellite services canadian satellite communications or cancom and through shaw broadcast services shaw direct one of canadas two national direct broadcast satellite providers for many years it also owned a number of radio stations and specialty television services these assets were later spun off into corus entertainment in an effort to satisfy a nowrepealed crtc policy discouraging crossownership of cablesystems and specialty services controversyedit internet usagebased billingedit in december  shaw filed complaints with the crtc to have competing internet video services such as netflix classified as broadcasters under canadian law in the same month shaw introduced usage based billing on internet plans and lowered plan caps an average of  while introducing overage fees of  to  per gigabyte on february   shaw agreed to put a hold on usage based billing for its services and to this date continues to not charge customers any overages for surpassing internet data caps complaintsedit customer service complaints are frequent among canadian cable mobile and internet users eponymous buildingsedit shaw barlow calgary shaw centre saskatoon shaw centre ottawa shaw park winnipeg shaw conference centre edmonton shaw court calgary head office shaw tower vancouver shaw ocean discovery centre  notforprofit cultural and learning centre sponsored by shaw communications sidney bc galleryedit shaw communications barlow office and call centre in calgary shaw conference centre edmonton shaw technician van with the previous logo see alsoedit companies portal burning log tv program canwest classicomm cybertipca list of assets owned by shaw communications media ownership in canada shaw tv telecom notesedit  a b c d shaw senior leadership shaw communications inc retrieved march     hardy ian april   alek krstajic is stepping down as ceo of freedom mobile mobilesyrup retrieved july     company profile for shaw communications inc sjr retrieved    shaw history shaw communications inc  retrieved    shaw cablesystems receives approval from crtc to purchase greater winnipeg cablevision canadian radio and telecommunications commission  retrieved    milestones shawca retrieved    canuck players plan splitting up of wic variety retrieved  march    corus lines up behind canuck shaws assets variety retrieved  march    pasco time warner to expand with shaw purchase retrieved  ju