w available to calgary customers the western canadian cable company announced wednesday the day before it reports results for the first quarter of  and holds its annual general meeting shaw is pitching the new service which it plans to launch in other markets in the coming months as a “bestinclass” premium tv product that comes with a voicecontrolled remote and advanced search functions “we are proud to be the first in canada to pioneer comcast’s groundbreaking technology and to be their first international partner” shaw ceo brad shaw said in a statement but it won’t be the last television provider to turn to comcast’s x platform after abandoning its internal attempts to create an iptv in  and taking a million writedown in the process rogers communications inc announced in december it too inked a deal with comcast x killing its own iptv development in a move that will result in a million to million writedown it will roll out the new technology in  the adoption of comcast’s platform comes as cable companies lose subscribers to traditional telephone companies bce inc in eastern canada and telus corp in the west stealing market share with their superior iptv services fibe tv and optic tv in the first nine months of  shaw and rogers respectively lost  and  tv subscribers while telus and bell gained  and  respectively comcast posted a net gain of  customers last year the first time its done so in the approximately eight years since launching the platform technology and product president tony werner said in a joint interview with shaw president jay mehr on wednesday “it’s iptv but it’s a lot more than that” werner said adding it uses cloudbased software that allows comcast to make changes to its offerings on the fly the voice remote has been a “huge success” with usage expected to double in  he said and the platform can be used for internet of things applications such as turning up a thermostat   mehr said the new tv product will help bring cord cutters cord shavers and cord nevers back into the cable system “this for sure is a differentiated video product” he said noting the variety of applications available including netflix he wouldn’t say exactly when he expects shaw to quell subscriber losses but said he expects it will gain traction more quickly than comcast did “it won’t take us that long” mehr said  comments share your thoughts fp tech desk worried about amazoncom dont be facebook brings its craigslistinspired marketplace to canada farewell ipod nano shuffle apple kills off two cheapest models in ipod line move over bill gates jeff bezos is now the worlds richest head off a trade war apple may skirt phone tariffs with  billion foxconn factory facebook just added  billion to its market value as shares surge to record high twitters stock is plunging this morning as monthly user growth evaporates cast your minds back to google — and know it still lives facebook results beat estimates as mobile ad sales soar  from video push nintendo doesnt believe in santa and neither should you twitter no longer at deaths door with recent  stock increase thursday earnings google canada head leaves company for weather network parent top stories watchhow brp caught a big wave while bombardier treads water brps stock is at alltime highs it has a new dividend and an ambitious growth plan meanwhile the former parent limps along canadas economic growth just blew past expectations — and you know what that means the data bolsters expectations for another interest rate hike from the bank of canada this year amazon’s earnings miss is being felt around the world this morning by abhinav ramnarayan london — an earnings miss by amazon that hit us technology stocks overnight rippled through into other markets on friday with asian stocks retreating from recent highs  check your flight status pearson airport ground workers are out on strike the gtaa warns that the ‘labour disruption may affect some flights’ this week in flyers find financial post on facebook s